\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish a mandatory standard of professional conduct for all personnel within the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 It defines the ethical obligations required to maintain the confidentiality,
 integrity,
 and availability of County information assets and ensures public trust in the administration of government technology.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County Information Operations personnel,
 including full-time employees,
 part-time staff,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 interns,
 and volunteers who access County IT systems or data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall conduct an annual review of this code and adjudicate complex ethical conflicts or exceptions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All IT Personnel
\series default
:
 Shall read,
 acknowledge,
 and adhere to this Code of Ethics and the referenced professional standards and report observed violations immediately.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Adherence to this policy is mandatory.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mandatory Reporting
\series default
:
 Personnel shall report known or suspected violations of this policy to their supervisor or the IT Director immediately.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Acknowledgment
\series default
:
 All Information Operations personnel shall sign an acknowledgment of this policy upon hire and annually thereafter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Sanctions
\series default
:
 Failure to comply with this policy shall result in disciplinary action,
 up to and including termination of employment or contract.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Formal Process
\series default
:
 The Department shall employ a formal sanctions process consistent with County HR policies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJIS Notification
\series default
:
 In accordance with 
\series bold
CJIS Security Policy 5.12
\series default
 and 
\series bold
NIST PS-8
\series default
,
 when a formal sanctions process is initiated against an individual with access to CJIS data,
 the IT Director shall notify the appropriate Information Security Officer (ISO),
 personnel security/HR representative,
 and System or Network Administrator within
\series bold
 twenty-four (24) hours
\series default
,
 identifying the individual sanctioned and the reason for the sanction unless County legal counsel determines a different timing is legally required.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Legal Consequences
\series default
:
 Misuse of CJIS data or County assets may result in civil and criminal prosecution under 
\series bold
NRS 205
\series default
 (Computer Crimes) and applicable Federal laws.
\end_layout

